1 olive oil
1 packet fusilli
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 punnet cherry tomatoes
1 diced bacon
1 packet basil pesto
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

Boil the kettle. Half-fill a
medium saucepan with
boiling water. Cook fusilli in
boiling water until ‘al dente’,
12 minutes. Drain and rinse
with cold water. Roughly
chop baby spinach leaves.
Halve cherry tomatoes.

Meanwhile, heat a medium
frying pan over high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook diced bacon, breaking
up with a spoon, until
golden, 4-5 minutes.

Add cooked pasta, basil
pesto, grated Parmesan
cheese and veggies to bacon
and stir to combine. Season
to taste. Divide pasta salad
between containers, allow to
cool completely. Refrigerate.